<section id="3-simple-steps" class="flex flex-col justify-between border-section  w-full h-[200vh]">
    <div id="1-register-cont" class="flex items-center justify-between border-parent   px-16 pt-4 w-full h-27-5pct">
        <div id="content" class="flex flex-col items-start border-child  w-1/2 h-full  ">
            <div id="1-register" class="flex items-center gap-4 border-img  w-full  py-8">
                <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 border-4 border-green-600 rounded-full">
                    <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">1</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-4xl font-semibold">
                    Register
                </p>
            </div>
            <div id="1-text" class="flex flex-col font-medium text-gray-700 text-[18px]  w-10/12  border-img   space-y-2">
                <p>Registration is free. Complete your profile by submitting your personal details
                    and housing preference (the type of house you are applying for).
                    Once registered, your details will be verified through the relevant Government offices.
                    To register, you must meet the conditions below:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside  px-2">
                    <li>Must be a <span class="font-bold">Kenyan Citizen</span></li>
                    <li>Must be above <span class="font-bold">18 years</span> of age</li>
                    <li>Must have a valid <span class="font-bold">National Identity Card</span></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div id="register-now" class="flex border-2 border-green-600 rounded-50px  px-8 py-4 mt-16">
                <span class="font-semibold">
                    Register now
                </span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="register-image" class="flex justify-center border-child w-1/2 h-full">
            <div class="flex border-img h-fit mb-6">
                <img src="images/3_easy_steps_1.png" alt="#" class="max-w-full h-auto mx-auto">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>



    <div id="2-save-cont" class="flex items-center justify-between border-parent bg-faces px-16 h-32-5pct  pt-12">
        <div id="register-image" class="flex justify-center border-child w-1/2 h-full">
            <div class="flex border-img h-fit mb-6">
                <img src="images/3_easy_steps_2.png" alt="#" class="">
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="content" class="flex flex-col items-start border-child  w-1/2 h-full  pl-36  ">
            <div id="2-save" class="flex items-center gap-4 border-img  w-full  py-8">
                <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 border-4 border-green-600 rounded-full">
                    <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">2</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-4xl font-semibold">
                    Save
                </p>
            </div>
            <div id="2-text" class="flex flex-col font-medium text-gray-700 text-[18px]  w-10/12  border-img  space-y-2">
                <p>Upon registration, you can start saving any amount you wish to your account on Boma Yangu.  </p>
                <p> You can save via USSD or through the payment options available on the web portal. </p> 
                <p>You can also view all the available projects on Boma Yangu and add them to your wish list or select them as your preferred unit. </p>
                <p> Selecting a preferred unit means that your savings will count towards the 10% deposit required for a unit to be allocated to you. Please note that:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside  px-2">
                    <li>Monthly saving are not capped </li>
                    <li>You can request a refund on your voluntary savings, which will not be taxed at time of withdrawal.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>




    <div id="3-own-cont" class="flex items-center justify-between border-parent px-16 h-27-5pct">
        <div id="content" class="flex flex-col items-start border-child  w-1/2 h-full">
            <div id="3-own" class="flex items-center gap-4 border-img  w-full  py-8">
                <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 border-4 border-green-600 rounded-full">
                    <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">3</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-4xl font-semibold">
                    Own
                </p>
            </div>
            <div id="1-text" class="flex flex-col font-medium text-gray-700 text-[18px]  w-10/12  border-img   space-y-2">
                <p> Allocation for available housing units is done through <span class="font-bold">a free, fair and transparent process.</span></p>
                <p> The initial eligibility for allocation will depend on several factors such as when you got to the 10% deposit as well as demand across the housing categories.</p>
                <p> Under the affordable housing scheme each Kenyan can only benefit once. Therefore, one Kenyan, one home will be enforced.</p>
                <p>Those who do not get an allocation in the initial allocation are then put on a waiting list to ensure they have priority in subsequent allocations.</p>
                <p>For private sector projects, allocation will be done according to the terms and conditions of sale.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="register-image" class="flex justify-center border-child w-1/2 h-full">
            <div class="flex border-img h-fit mb-6">
                <img src="images/3_easy_steps_3.png" alt="#" class="max-w-full h-auto mx-auto">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>





    <div id="4-who-we-serve-cont" class="flex items-center justify-between border-parent px-16 h-12-5pct">
        <div class="flex flex-col w-1/2">
            <p class="text-4xl font-semibold  mb-4">Who we serve</p>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-700 text-[18px] mb-2">The Affordable Housing Programme is a priority initiative under the government which is geared towards facilitating the production of decent, safe and affordable housing for citizens of Kenya.</p>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-700 text-[18px]">Beyond catering to home applicants, the program incorporates supply, demand, and creates an enabling environment through policy interventions.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


